<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4759372>
    bibo:endPage "155" ;
    bibo:issue "13" ;
    bibo:journal "Illiesia" ;
    bibo:startPage "146" ;
    bibo:volume "5" ;
    dc:creator "Sandberg, John B." ;
    dc:date "2009" ;
    dc:title "Vibrational Communication (Drumming) Of The Western Nearctic Stonefly Genus Hesperoperla (Plecoptera: Perlidae)" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4759385>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4759378>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4759380> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4759385>
    dc:description "Fig. 6. Hesperoperla pacifica complex monophasic-grouped call patterns based upon individual average interbeat intervals i1-i7 and average inter-group intervals igi1-igi14 (msec) for one Butte Creek (BC) and two Domingo Spring (DS) 2007 analysis groups. A) White bars = BC reared male calls (N=120), B) Gray bars = DS collected male calls (N=69) and C) Black bars = DS reared male calls (N=22). Y-axis ranges from 50-250 msec." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4759385/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4759378>
    dc:description "Fig.3. Hesperoperla pacificadrumming.A. 3-way exchange, ♂Cmonophasicand grouped, ♀and ♂Rmonophasic answerand response respectively. B. Male call with 1st monophasic beat followed by 16 grouped signals. Reared from Butte Creek, Butte Co., CA, J. Sandberg, April 2007. d = (♀-♂R) exchange interval, e = inter-group interval, f = intra-group interval." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4759378/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4759380>
    dc:description "Fig. 4. Hesperoperla pacifica drumming. A. Male call with 1st, 2nd and 7th beats monophasic and the others grouped. B. 3-way exchange. Reared from Domingo Spring, Plumas Co., CA, J. Sandberg, June 2007." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4759380/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

